"# Amazon DynamoDB\n\n**DynamoDB is a fully managed NoSQL database service** provided by AWS that delivers single-digit millisecond performance at any scale.\n\n## Key Characteristics\n\n- **Serverless**: No servers to provision, patch, or manage\n- **Fast and consistent**: Single-digit millisecond latency at any scale\n- **Highly available**: Built-in replication across multiple Availability Zones\n- **Flexible**: Supports both key-value and document data models\n- **Scalable**: Automatically scales throughput capacity up or down based on demand\n\n## Core Features\n\n**Table Structure**: Data is organized into tables, items (rows), and attributes (columns)\n\n**Primary Keys**: Two types:\n- **Partition key**: Simple primary key for unique item identification\n- **Partition key + Sort key**: Composite key for organizing related data\n\n**Read/Write Modes**:\n- **On-demand**: Pay per request, scales automatically\n- **Provisioned**: Specify read/write capacity units for predictable workloads\n\n**Secondary Indexes**:\n- **Global Secondary Index (GSI)**: Different partition and sort keys\n- **Local Secondary Index (LSI)**: Same partition key, different sort key\n\n## Common Use Cases\n\n- Web and mobile application backends\n- Gaming leaderboards and session storage\n- IoT data storage and real-time analytics\n- Shopping carts and user profiles\n- Serverless architectures with Lambda\n\n## Best Practices\n\n- Design partition keys to distribute data evenly\n- Use DynamoDB Streams for event-driven architectures\n- Enable point-in-time recovery for critical data\n- Use global tables for multi-region replication"